<L>That courts jilt Fortune for a bride.</L>
<L>This par'di&s;e-tree, &s;o fair and high,</L>
<L>I view with no a&s;piring eye:</L>
<L>Like a&s;pine &s;hake the re&s;tle&s;s leaves,</L>
<L>And Sodom-fruit our pains deceives,</L>
<L>Whence frequent falls give no &s;urprize,</L>
<L>But fits of Spleen, call'd <HI>growing wi&s;e.</HI></L>
<L>Greatne&s;s in glitt'ring forms di&s;play'd</L>
