<L>Gives &s;elf-deba&s;ing fits of Spleen.</L>
<L>We &s;hould be pleas'd that things are &s;o,</L>
<L>Who do for nothing &s;ee the &s;how,</L>
<L>And, middle-&s;iz'd, can pa&s;s between</L>
<L>Life's hubbub &s;afe, becau&s;e un&s;een,</L>
<L>And 'mid&s;t the glare of greatne&s;s trace</L>
