</LG>
<LG>
<PB N="142" REF="144">
<L>Th' enthu&s;ia&s;t's hopes, and raptures wild</L>
<L>Have never yet my rea&s;on foil'd.</L>
<L>His &s;pringy &s;oul dilates like air,</L>
<L>When free from weight of ambient care,</L>
<L>And, hu&s;h'd in meditation deep,</L>
<L>Slides into dreams, as when a&s;leep;</L>
<L>Then, fond of new di&s;coveries grown,</L>
<L>Proves a Columbus of her own,</L>
<L>Di&s;dains the narrow bounds of place,</L>
