</LG>
<LG>
<L><NOTE N="y" PLACE="foot"><L>Imberbis juvenis, tandem cu&s;tode remoto,</L>
<L>Gaudet equis canibu&s;que, &amp; aprici gramine campi;</L>
<L>Cereus in vitium flecti, monitoribus a&s;per,</L>
<L>Utilium tardus provi&s;or, prodigus aeris,</L>
<L>Sublimis cupidu&s;que, &amp; amata relinquere pernix.</L></NOTE>More loves the youth, ju&s;t come to his e&s;tate,</L>
<L>To range the fields, than in the hou&s;e debate;</L>
<L>More he delights in fav'rite Jowler's tongue,</L>
<L>Than in Will Shippen, or Sir William Yonge:</L>
<L>If in one cha&s;e he can two hor&s;es kill,</L>
<L>He cares not two-pence for the land-tax bill:</L>
<L>Loud in his wine, in women not o'er nice,</L>
<L>He damns his uncles if they give advice;</L>
<L>Votes as his father did when there's a call,</L>
