<L>Thinks nothing rightly done &s;ince &s;eventy-eight,</L>
<L>Swears pre&s;ent members do not talk, but prate:</L>
<L>In Charles the &s;econd's days, &s;ays he, ye prigs,</L>
<L>Tories were Tories then, and Whigs were Whigs.</L>
<L>Alas! this is a lamentable truth,</L>
<L>We lo&s;e in age, as we advance in youth:</L>
